In parallelogram $ABCD$, angle $B$ measures $110^\circ$. What is the number of degrees in the measure of angle $C$?
inference:
Since both pairs of opposite angles in a parallelogram are congruent, we have
$$m\angle D=m\angle B=110^\circ$$
Since the sum of the angles in a parallelogram is $360^\circ$, we have
$$m\angle A+m\angle B+m\angle C+m\angle D=360^\circ$$
$$\Rightarrow m\angle A+110^\circ+m\angle C+110^\circ=360^\circ$$
$$\Rightarrow m\angle A+m\angle C+220^\circ=360^\circ$$
$$\Rightarrow m\angle A+m\angle C=360^\circ-220^\circ=140^\circ$$
Since both pairs of opposite angles in a parallelogram are congruent, we have
$$m\angle A=m\angle C$$
$$\Rightarrow m\angle A+m\angle A=140^\circ$$
$$\Rightarrow 2m\angle A=140^\circ$$
$$\Rightarrow m\angle A=70^\circ$$
Therefore,
$$m\angle C=\boxed{70^\circ}.$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{70^\circ}.$ I hope it is correct.
